[blows landing]
[all grunting]

00:04:00.213 --> 00:04:02.151
<i>[Tatsuya] Looks like</i>
<i>the melee's already started.</i>

00:04:02.217 --> 00:04:03.821
[Leonhard grunting]

00:04:03.888 --> 00:04:04.856
Leo!

00:04:04.923 --> 00:04:06.192
[Leonhard] Heads up!

00:04:06.259 --> 00:04:08.496
[shouting]

00:04:08.564 --> 00:04:10.000
[blow lands]
[groans]

00:04:10.066 --> 00:04:12.906
Leo's CAD is voice activated?
That's rare.

00:04:12.972 --> 00:04:13.941
Hey, Brother,

00:04:14.008 --> 00:04:15.477
he's executing
and building sequences.

00:04:15.545 --> 00:04:16.647
You're correct.

00:04:16.713 --> 00:04:18.416
He's executing
his spells sequentially.

00:04:18.483 --> 00:04:20.320
That was popular ten years ago.

00:04:20.387 --> 00:04:23.326
[Erika] Wow.
Even his magic's old school.

00:04:23.393 --> 00:04:24.495
[both grunting]

00:04:24.563 --> 00:04:27.401
Whoa!
How's his CAD still okay?

00:04:27.735 --> 00:04:29.739
[Tatsuya] It's
his fortifying spell cast

00:04:29.806 --> 00:04:31.209
on the CAD itself.

00:04:31.275 --> 00:04:32.512
[grunting]

00:04:32.579 --> 00:04:34.516
[Erika] So no matter
how violently

00:04:34.583 --> 00:04:36.620
he throws that thing around,
it won't break?

00:04:36.687 --> 00:04:38.591
That sort of magic
was made for him.

00:04:38.657 --> 00:04:40.460
Leo, we're going on ahead!

00:04:40.528 --> 00:04:41.730
[blow lands]
[grunts]

00:04:41.797 --> 00:04:43.601
Great idea!
Best of luck to ya!

00:04:44.536 --> 00:04:46.507
All right, then!
Bring it!

00:04:55.858 --> 00:04:58.797
[low humming]

00:05:02.037 --> 00:05:04.008
<i>[Tatsuya] Two of them</i>
<i>at the foot of the staircase.</i>

00:05:05.978 --> 00:05:08.551
<i>Another one's at the top</i>
<i>of the stairs.</i>

00:05:11.289 --> 00:05:13.861
<i>Four in the second floor's</i>
<i>special reading room.</i>

00:05:17.067 --> 00:05:18.203
By my count.

00:05:18.269 --> 00:05:20.340
Incredible!
With you around,

00:05:20.407 --> 00:05:22.846
they've got zero chance
of ambushing us.

00:05:23.079 --> 00:05:25.050
I definitely wouldn't wanna
go up against you

00:05:25.116 --> 00:05:26.452
in a real battle scenario.

00:05:26.520 --> 00:05:28.289
I wonder what the terrorists
are plotting

00:05:28.356 --> 00:05:29.726
in the special reading room.

00:05:29.793 --> 00:05:32.030
My best guess
is those insurgents upstairs

00:05:32.097 --> 00:05:33.934
are trying to steal
the Magic University's

00:05:34.001 --> 00:05:35.070
classified materials.

00:05:35.136 --> 00:05:36.005
[rustling]
[both gasping]

00:05:36.072 --> 00:05:37.909
[grunting]

00:05:40.748 --> 00:05:42.251
Who are you?
Stop!

00:05:42.317 --> 00:05:43.587
[both grunting]

00:05:43.654 --> 00:05:44.589
[blow lands]
[man groans]

00:05:44.656 --> 00:05:46.425
‐ [grunts]
‐ [groaning]

00:05:46.960 --> 00:05:48.797
‐ [exhales sharply]
‐ [Tatsuya] Erika.

00:05:49.933 --> 00:05:51.335
‐ [Boy] Who's there?
‐ [gasps]

00:05:51.904 --> 00:05:53.273
[shouts]

00:05:53.339 --> 00:05:54.341
[both grunting]

00:05:54.408 --> 00:05:55.878
Just leave this idiot to me!

00:05:56.379 --> 00:05:57.314
Very well.

00:05:57.381 --> 00:05:58.651
[both grunting]

00:06:05.363 --> 00:06:06.733
[phone beeping]

00:06:07.635 --> 00:06:09.438
[digital whooshing]

00:06:17.354 --> 00:06:19.526
[Sayaka] I thought our goal
was to end discrimination based

00:06:19.593 --> 00:06:20.795
<i>on magic.</i>

00:06:21.062 --> 00:06:22.064
<i>So why?</i>

00:06:22.130 --> 00:06:23.099
<i>Why would they require all</i>

00:06:23.166 --> 00:06:24.903
<i>of this cutting‐edge</i>
<i>magic research?</i>

00:06:25.504 --> 00:06:26.607
<i>Is this it?</i>

00:06:26.673 --> 00:06:28.376
<i>Is this what I wanted to do?</i>

00:06:28.443 --> 00:06:30.447
[beeping]
[Boy] Yes, it opened!

00:06:30.948 --> 00:06:33.152
[Boy 2] We can finally access
this country's

00:06:33.219 --> 00:06:34.221
cutting‐edge research.

00:06:34.288 --> 00:06:35.591
[Boy] Copy over the data.

00:06:35.658 --> 00:06:37.194
Get me a recordable cube.

00:06:37.261 --> 00:06:38.631
[Boy 3] Right.

00:06:38.998 --> 00:06:39.933
The‐‐the door!

00:06:41.870 --> 00:06:42.906
[all gasping]

00:06:45.578 --> 00:06:46.580
[Tatsuya] Game's over.

00:06:46.647 --> 00:06:48.316
[magical whooshing]

00:06:48.383 --> 00:06:49.819
[Boy] What?
[shouts]

00:06:50.253 --> 00:06:51.823
[groans]

00:06:51.890 --> 00:06:54.829
Your pathetic master plan
is now history.

00:06:54.896 --> 00:06:56.032
Shiba, but...

00:06:58.971 --> 00:07:00.006
Damn you!

00:07:00.073 --> 00:07:01.008
[gasps]

00:07:02.477 --> 00:07:07.822
[shouting]

00:07:07.889 --> 00:07:10.060
[Miyuki] Don't attempt
anything foolish.

00:07:10.126 --> 00:07:12.431
There's no way that
any malicious intent towards

00:07:12.497 --> 00:07:14.134
my brother could escape me.

00:07:14.536 --> 00:07:16.405
[Tatsuya] Sayaka Mibu,
this is reality.

00:07:16.472 --> 00:07:17.474
[gasps]

00:07:17.542 --> 00:07:18.577
[Tatsuya] A world where everyone

00:07:18.644 --> 00:07:20.548
is treated equally
is a fantasy.

00:07:20.615 --> 00:07:22.919
Such a place could never exist.

00:07:23.754 --> 00:07:25.591
If there was a world
of equality where talent

00:07:25.658 --> 00:07:27.662
and aptitude didn't matter...

00:07:28.096 --> 00:07:31.536
Then every one of us would be
equally snubbed there as well.

00:07:31.937 --> 00:07:34.509
You were being used,
Miss Mibu.

00:07:35.110 --> 00:07:37.147
This is the reality
of that ideal,

00:07:37.214 --> 00:07:39.953
which sounded so sweet when it
was whispered to you.

00:07:41.122 --> 00:07:42.558
But why?

00:07:42.625 --> 00:07:44.328
How'd this even happen to me?

00:07:44.395 --> 00:07:46.667
Are you saying trying
to wipe out discrimination

00:07:46.733 --> 00:07:47.702
was a mistake?

00:07:47.769 --> 00:07:49.471
I'm sure that you yourself

00:07:49.539 --> 00:07:51.075
grew up being
constantly compared

00:07:51.142 --> 00:07:52.444
to your talented sister,

00:07:52.512 --> 00:07:53.747
and there's no way
you didn't suffer

00:07:53.814 --> 00:07:55.450
from unjust humiliation!

00:07:55.518 --> 00:07:58.557
I'm sure you've been mocked
by everybody around you, too!

00:08:00.093 --> 00:08:01.797
[Miyuki] I have never
held any contempt

00:08:01.863 --> 00:08:02.965
for my older brother.

00:08:03.032 --> 00:08:04.134
[gasps]

00:08:04.201 --> 00:08:06.172
It wouldn't make any difference
if everyone else

00:08:06.238 --> 00:08:08.577
on the face of the planet
but me were to slander,

00:08:08.644 --> 00:08:11.449
disparage,
and even mock my older brother.

00:08:11.850 --> 00:08:13.286
<i>[Miyuki] In spite of it all,</i>

00:08:13.353 --> 00:08:17.695
<i>I grant him as much love</i>
<i>and respect as I always have.</i>

00:08:18.731 --> 00:08:19.999
<i>It's true.</i>

00:08:20.066 --> 00:08:21.770
<i>There are many ignorant people</i>

00:08:21.837 --> 00:08:23.741
<i>who look down</i>
<i>on my older brother,</i>

00:08:23.807 --> 00:08:26.245
<i>but there are far more people</i>
<i>who recognize</i>

00:08:26.312 --> 00:08:29.284
<i>and even celebrate</i>
<i>how splendid Tatsuya is.</i>

00:08:29.351 --> 00:08:31.055
So, Miss Mibu,

00:08:31.122 --> 00:08:33.226
I must admit that I feel sorry
for you.

00:08:33.292 --> 00:08:34.461
[Sayaka] What did you say?

00:08:34.529 --> 00:08:36.065
Wasn't there anybody
in your life

00:08:36.132 --> 00:08:38.837
who appreciated you
for the talented person you are?

00:08:38.904 --> 00:08:41.375
Was your magical prowess
the exclusive barometer

00:08:41.442 --> 00:08:42.745
by which you were measured?

00:08:42.812 --> 00:08:45.518
My brother here
certainly acknowledged you.

00:08:45.584 --> 00:08:46.586
[gasps]

00:08:46.653 --> 00:08:48.524
Your kendo swordplay skill set,

00:08:48.590 --> 00:08:49.893
your undeniable beauty.

00:08:49.959 --> 00:08:51.128
[whimpers]

00:08:51.730 --> 00:08:54.368
But those are both
such superficial things.

00:08:54.435 --> 00:08:56.472
[Miyuki] But they're a part
of who you really are.

00:08:56.540 --> 00:08:57.608
[whimpers]

00:08:57.675 --> 00:08:59.813
Those are things
that make you attractive

00:08:59.879 --> 00:09:02.117
and help define who you are,
don't they?

00:09:02.585 --> 00:09:04.021
[Miyuki] You
and my older brother

00:09:04.088 --> 00:09:06.058
have only just met,
remember?

00:09:06.860 --> 00:09:09.098
What exactly were you seeking
from him?

00:09:09.699 --> 00:09:10.935
Well, I...

00:09:11.570 --> 00:09:12.572
In the end,

00:09:12.638 --> 00:09:13.974
there was no one in your life

00:09:14.041 --> 00:09:17.648
who despised you as a Weed more
than you yourself.

00:09:18.116 --> 00:09:19.418
[gasps]

00:09:19.485 --> 00:09:20.755
‐ [Boy] Mibu!
‐ [gasps]

00:09:20.821 --> 00:09:22.157
Use this ring!

00:09:23.259 --> 00:09:24.696
[gasps]

00:09:26.633 --> 00:09:28.035
<i>[Tatsuya] Cast jamming, huh?</i>

00:09:28.102 --> 00:09:29.138
Brother!

00:09:32.377 --> 00:09:33.981
[both shouting]

00:09:34.047 --> 00:09:35.518
[blows landing]
[both grunting]

00:09:35.584 --> 00:09:36.653
[tools rattling on floor]

00:09:36.720 --> 00:09:38.022
[Sayaka breathing heavily]

00:09:39.626 --> 00:09:41.295
[Tatsuya] Miyuki, back off.

00:09:41.362 --> 00:09:42.865
[gasps]
But Brother...

00:09:43.299 --> 00:09:45.470
Shouldn't we have taken Mibu
into custody?

00:09:45.905 --> 00:09:47.775
When you don't have
good visibility,

00:09:47.842 --> 00:09:49.278
<i>you shouldn't push yourself</i>
<i>too hard.</i>

00:09:49.344 --> 00:09:50.246
[breathing heavily]

00:09:51.115 --> 00:09:51.883
Besides...

00:09:51.950 --> 00:09:54.021
[breathing heavily]

00:09:54.087 --> 00:09:56.492
<i>[Tatsuya] I'm sure she'll</i>
<i>capture her for us.</i>

00:09:56.560 --> 00:09:57.728
[panting, grunts]

00:09:57.795 --> 00:09:58.797
Who are you?

00:09:58.864 --> 00:10:00.467
It's very nice to meet you.

00:10:00.534 --> 00:10:01.703
I'm Erika Chiba.

00:10:01.770 --> 00:10:03.540
I'm a student of class 1E.

00:10:03.607 --> 00:10:04.909
You're Sayaka Mibu,

00:10:04.976 --> 00:10:06.178
the runner up in the national

00:10:06.245 --> 00:10:08.449
junior high school girls'
kendo tournament.

00:10:08.517 --> 00:10:10.019
Year before last,
isn't that right?

00:10:10.086 --> 00:10:12.257
Yeah, what's it matter to you?
[grunts]

00:10:12.324 --> 00:10:13.392
[Erika] Nothing.

00:10:13.459 --> 00:10:16.065
I just wanted to confirm
that it's really you.

00:10:17.400 --> 00:10:18.537
[grunts]

00:10:18.604 --> 00:10:20.206
[Erika] Hey, no need
to panic here.

00:10:20.273 --> 00:10:22.477
I can wait for you to get
your hands on a weapon.

00:10:22.545 --> 00:10:23.680
[gasps]

00:10:25.350 --> 00:10:27.053
[grunting]

00:10:27.120 --> 00:10:28.590
You should get out of my way!

00:10:28.657 --> 00:10:30.126
Don't make an enemy of me!

00:10:30.594 --> 00:10:33.499
Well, now that you've said that,
isn't this self defense?

00:10:33.934 --> 00:10:35.003
Not that I'm going

00:10:35.069 --> 00:10:36.773
to be making up excuses
like that.

00:10:37.708 --> 00:10:39.111
[Erika] Okay,

00:10:39.178 --> 00:10:41.382
how 'bout we have ourselves
a serious sword fight?

00:10:41.448 --> 00:10:42.384
You in?

00:10:45.791 --> 00:10:47.093
‐ [grunts]
‐ So quick!

00:10:47.160 --> 00:10:49.131
[blows landing]
[both grunting]

00:10:50.166 --> 00:10:51.302
[shouts]

00:10:51.703 --> 00:10:52.839
[grunts]

00:10:52.905 --> 00:10:54.374
Self acceleration?

00:10:54.742 --> 00:10:56.445
Same spell used by Mari?

00:10:56.513 --> 00:10:57.548
[gasps]

00:10:57.615 --> 00:10:58.784
[grunts]

