00:11:12.745 --> 00:11:14.147
[shouts]

00:11:16.118 --> 00:11:17.220
[gasps]

00:11:18.222 --> 00:11:19.324
[grunts]

00:11:19.391 --> 00:11:20.861
Now pick it up.

00:11:22.532 --> 00:11:25.571
I want to see you go all out.
Don't you dare hold back.

00:11:26.005 --> 00:11:28.644
The spectre of that woman
who ensnares you,

00:11:28.710 --> 00:11:30.446
I'll smash it into oblivion.

00:11:30.514 --> 00:11:31.716
[gasps]

00:11:31.783 --> 00:11:33.052
[grunts]
[drops weapon on floor]

00:11:34.154 --> 00:11:36.158
I won't be relying on this,
then.

00:11:40.133 --> 00:11:42.170
[Sayaka] I'm going to demolish
that move...

00:11:44.141 --> 00:11:46.111
With the use
of my intrinsic power!

00:11:46.980 --> 00:11:48.249
It's obvious to me.

00:11:50.521 --> 00:11:52.090
That speed technique,

00:11:52.157 --> 00:11:54.461
it's the same
as Miss Watanabe's!

00:11:54.529 --> 00:11:55.764
On the contrary,

00:11:55.831 --> 00:11:56.967
there's more than a bit
of a difference

00:11:57.033 --> 00:11:58.670
between my technique and hers.

00:11:58.737 --> 00:12:01.643
<i>[techno music]</i>

00:12:01.710 --> 00:12:08.924
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:12:09.191 --> 00:12:10.126
[grunts]

00:12:10.193 --> 00:12:11.128
[gasps]

00:12:11.195 --> 00:12:12.264
[groans]

00:12:16.940 --> 00:12:18.409
[Erika] Sorry.

00:12:18.844 --> 00:12:21.081
It appears I might
have broken your arm.

00:12:21.448 --> 00:12:23.319
[Sayaka groaning]

00:12:23.386 --> 00:12:25.223
It's fractured for sure.

00:12:25.290 --> 00:12:26.358
I don't mind.

00:12:26.425 --> 00:12:28.730
It means you refused
to hold back.

00:12:28.797 --> 00:12:30.066
Right.

00:12:30.133 --> 00:12:31.770
You can hold your head up high,
Miss Mibu,

00:12:31.836 --> 00:12:34.676
because you played for keeps
with a daughter of the Chiba.

00:12:34.742 --> 00:12:35.911
Hold on, then.

00:12:35.978 --> 00:12:37.581
You're a member
of that Chiba family?

00:12:37.648 --> 00:12:39.484
As a matter of fact,
I am.

00:12:39.552 --> 00:12:42.892
Incidentally,
Watanabe's a disciple of ours.

00:12:42.959 --> 00:12:46.131
Mari Watanabe is a mokuroku,
and I'm an inka.

00:12:46.198 --> 00:12:47.969
When you compare
our kenjutsu skills,

00:12:48.035 --> 00:12:49.104
I'm better than she is.

00:12:49.171 --> 00:12:50.273
[exhales]

00:12:50.741 --> 00:12:51.910
I see.

00:12:53.446 --> 00:12:54.749
[grunts]

00:12:56.285 --> 00:12:57.253
Hmm.

00:13:03.834 --> 00:13:05.336
‐ [Koutarou] Hey, Tsukasa.
‐ Hmm?

00:13:05.403 --> 00:13:08.042
Oh, hi, Tatsumi.
Can I help you?

00:13:09.444 --> 00:13:11.883
Yes, indeed.
I've got a question to ask you.

00:13:12.384 --> 00:13:13.386
A‐‐Ask me?

00:13:13.452 --> 00:13:14.421
[Koutarou] Yeah.

00:13:14.488 --> 00:13:16.291
My chairwoman
has what some people

00:13:16.358 --> 00:13:18.462
might call a sketchy kind
of skill.

00:13:18.530 --> 00:13:20.400
By manipulating air currents

00:13:20.466 --> 00:13:22.638
and combining
multiple fragrances,

00:13:22.705 --> 00:13:24.709
she can whip up
a truth serum without using

00:13:24.776 --> 00:13:26.245
any illegal drugs.

00:13:26.312 --> 00:13:27.247
[gasps]

00:13:27.314 --> 00:13:29.117
Because of that,
now we know.

00:13:29.184 --> 00:13:32.658
We have evidence that it
was you pulling all the strings.

00:13:32.725 --> 00:13:34.662
‐ [panting]
‐ Hold it!

00:13:35.063 --> 00:13:37.768
Mr. Tsukasa, please,
come along quietly with us.

00:13:37.835 --> 00:13:39.972
[grunting]

00:13:41.108 --> 00:13:42.277
[both grunting]

00:13:42.344 --> 00:13:43.947
[groans]

00:13:44.682 --> 00:13:46.051
[Kinoe thuds on ground]

00:13:53.366 --> 00:13:56.372
[indistinct chatter]
[sirens blaring]

00:14:00.881 --> 00:14:02.117
<i>[Sayaka] For over a year now,</i>

00:14:02.183 --> 00:14:04.121
<i>Captain Tsukasa</i>
<i>has been extorting</i>

00:14:04.187 --> 00:14:05.991
<i>the whole kendo team</i>
<i>to finally bring about</i>

00:14:06.058 --> 00:14:08.496
an end to unfair discrimination
<i>by magic.</i>

00:14:09.665 --> 00:14:11.168
The captain once lured me

00:14:11.235 --> 00:14:13.840
to Blanche's
local branch office as well.

00:14:14.509 --> 00:14:17.915
Apparently, his brother
is head of the Japan branch.

00:14:20.721 --> 00:14:22.992
[Sayaka] Only a few days
after enrolling here,

00:14:23.059 --> 00:14:24.829
someone had discriminated
against me

00:14:24.896 --> 00:14:26.533
as a course two student.

00:14:27.200 --> 00:14:28.904
I think that's why I listened
so intently

00:14:28.970 --> 00:14:30.139
to what the captain said.

00:14:30.206 --> 00:14:32.678
How had they discriminated
against you?

00:14:33.045 --> 00:14:34.481
[whimpers]

00:14:34.549 --> 00:14:35.584
[grunts]

00:14:36.653 --> 00:14:37.755
It was...

00:14:38.289 --> 00:14:39.625
[Sayaka]
The kenjutsu team caused

00:14:39.692 --> 00:14:41.395
a disturbance while recruiting.

00:14:41.462 --> 00:14:43.834
I saw Miss Watanabe's
magic sword skills

00:14:43.900 --> 00:14:45.036
when she stopped it.

00:14:45.103 --> 00:14:46.806
I was speechless.

00:14:47.508 --> 00:14:50.781
So right away I asked her if she
would be a mentor to me,

00:14:50.848 --> 00:14:52.785
but she coldly brushed me off.

00:14:52.852 --> 00:14:53.887
What's that?

00:14:53.954 --> 00:14:55.189
[grunts]

00:14:55.557 --> 00:14:58.129
<i>[Mari] Mibu,</i>
<i>did that really happen?</i>

00:14:58.195 --> 00:15:00.032
<i>[Sayaka] You said,</i>
<i>"You're no match for me.</i>

00:15:00.099 --> 00:15:01.368
<i>"It would be a waste.</i>

00:15:01.435 --> 00:15:03.272
<i>"Go pick out an opponent</i>
<i>you're worthy of.</i>

00:15:03.339 --> 00:15:04.107
<i>Go."</i>

00:15:04.174 --> 00:15:05.544
<i>[Mari gasps]</i>

00:15:05.611 --> 00:15:07.280
<i>[Sayaka] I thought it</i>
<i>was because I</i>

00:15:07.347 --> 00:15:09.451
<i>was a course two student.</i>
<i>The thought of that‐‐</i>

00:15:09.519 --> 00:15:11.790
[Mari] Wait a second.
I remember now.

00:15:11.856 --> 00:15:14.060
I know exactly what happened
that day.

00:15:14.127 --> 00:15:16.666
Listen, I swear it
was never my intention

00:15:16.733 --> 00:15:17.701
to brush you off,
all right?

00:15:17.768 --> 00:15:19.037
What?

00:15:19.104 --> 00:15:21.308
Correct me if I'm wrong,
but this is what I said.

00:15:22.110 --> 00:15:23.312
"With my sword skills,

00:15:23.379 --> 00:15:25.316
I could never hope
to be a match for you."

00:15:25.717 --> 00:15:28.155
"It would be much better for you
if you practice with someone

00:15:28.222 --> 00:15:31.930
who's worthy of you,"
didn't I?

00:15:31.996 --> 00:15:33.700
Huh?
So you mean...

00:15:35.036 --> 00:15:36.338
<i>[Erika] Wait a sec, Mari.</i>

00:15:36.405 --> 00:15:38.543
<i>So you're saying</i>
<i>that you declined</i>

00:15:38.610 --> 00:15:40.881
<i>to practice with Mibu</i>
<i>because she was the one</i>

00:15:40.948 --> 00:15:42.183
<i>who's stronger than you?</i>

00:15:42.618 --> 00:15:44.755
<i>[Mari] Well, obviously</i>
<i>if magic were involved,</i>

00:15:44.822 --> 00:15:46.693
my skill set might be superior,

00:15:46.759 --> 00:15:49.264
<i>but Mibu has trained</i>
<i>in pure swordsmanship.</i>

00:15:49.331 --> 00:15:51.468
<i>No way can I beat her</i>
<i>with my sword.</i>

00:15:51.703 --> 00:15:55.744
[Sayaka] Then it was all nothing
<i>more than a misunderstanding?</i>

00:15:55.811 --> 00:15:57.180
[groans]

00:15:59.986 --> 00:16:01.188
<i>[Sayaka] No way.</i>

00:16:01.255 --> 00:16:02.658
<i>[whimpering]</i>

00:16:02.725 --> 00:16:04.461
<i>I'm such an idiot!</i>

00:16:04.529 --> 00:16:07.500
[crying weakly]

00:16:07.868 --> 00:16:12.010
I just assumed,
misunderstanding you like that.

00:16:12.945 --> 00:16:15.316
Always beating myself up
over it.

00:16:15.383 --> 00:16:18.523
Wasting the past year
by resenting your kindness.

00:16:21.028 --> 00:16:22.397
[Tatsuya] I don't think
it was a waste.

00:16:24.367 --> 00:16:25.537
Tatsuya.

00:16:26.004 --> 00:16:27.808
In fact,
this is what Erika said...

00:16:28.309 --> 00:16:29.545
[Tatsuya] After your fight,

00:16:29.612 --> 00:16:31.649
that you had become
so much more powerful

00:16:31.716 --> 00:16:33.285
than in junior high.

00:16:33.954 --> 00:16:36.926
Which is the undeniable result
of the skills you worked

00:16:36.993 --> 00:16:39.464
so hard to polish
with your own two hands.

00:16:39.532 --> 00:16:41.903
Instead of wallowing
in your resentment,

00:16:41.970 --> 00:16:43.974
or merely drowning
in your sorrows,

00:16:44.040 --> 00:16:45.777
you kept growing
and improving yourself

00:16:45.844 --> 00:16:48.884
so there's no way this past year
could be considered a waste

00:16:48.950 --> 00:16:50.253
of your time,
Miss Mibu.

00:16:50.687 --> 00:16:51.789
Tatsuya.

00:16:51.856 --> 00:16:53.425
[whimpers]

00:16:53.492 --> 00:16:56.666
There's one thing I'd like
to request of you.

00:16:56.733 --> 00:16:58.002
What's that?

00:16:58.068 --> 00:17:01.108
Please just don't move
for a second.

00:17:01.743 --> 00:17:05.016
[Sayaka crying]

00:17:25.757 --> 00:17:27.026
[Tatsuya] Now, then.

00:17:27.661 --> 00:17:30.132
Where are the people
from Blanche right now?

00:17:30.199 --> 00:17:32.036
I'll be needing to know
where I can find them.

00:17:32.103 --> 00:17:33.239
[gasps]

00:17:33.305 --> 00:17:35.176
Tatsuya, don't tell me that‐‐

00:17:35.243 --> 00:17:37.080
you're not taking them on
in battle, are you?

00:17:37.514 --> 00:17:38.984
That's not
an accurate description

00:17:39.050 --> 00:17:40.152
of what I'll do.

00:17:40.219 --> 00:17:41.723
I'm going to demolish them.

00:17:41.789 --> 00:17:42.891
It's dangerous.

00:17:42.958 --> 00:17:44.795
That's not for a student to do.

00:17:44.862 --> 00:17:46.131
[Mayumi] I'm against it, too.

00:17:46.198 --> 00:17:47.902
We should leave
non‐school‐related issues

00:17:47.968 --> 00:17:48.837
to law enforcement.

00:17:48.904 --> 00:17:50.339
Okay.

00:17:50.707 --> 00:17:52.310
[Tatsuya] Will you be sending
Miss Mibu to court

00:17:52.377 --> 00:17:53.680
for attempted robbery?

00:17:53.747 --> 00:17:54.682
[both gasping]

00:17:55.349 --> 00:17:56.619
That's a good point.

00:17:56.686 --> 00:17:59.491
Intervention from
the police would be undesirable.

00:17:59.926 --> 00:18:01.428
Even with that being the case,
we students can't let this go.

00:18:03.700 --> 00:18:06.906
But still, Tatsuya,
we're talking terrorists here.

00:18:06.973 --> 00:18:09.679
None of us student
authority figures would dare

00:18:09.745 --> 00:18:12.317
to ask any classmates
to risk their lives.

00:18:12.383 --> 00:18:14.321
I would expect nothing less.

00:18:14.956 --> 00:18:16.592
And it was never my intention

00:18:16.659 --> 00:18:18.630
to ask the student council
for help.

00:18:19.064 --> 00:18:20.968
Are you planning to go alone?

00:18:21.502 --> 00:18:23.072
Normally that
is what I would prefer.

00:18:23.138 --> 00:18:24.274
However‐‐

00:18:24.341 --> 00:18:25.744
‐ I'm going with you.
‐ [exhales]

00:18:26.211 --> 00:18:28.015
‐ And I'll come with!
‐ I will, too.

00:18:28.082 --> 00:18:29.250
[gasps]

00:18:29.317 --> 00:18:30.520
No, Tatsuya!

00:18:30.587 --> 00:18:31.990
If you're doing this
for my sake,

00:18:32.056 --> 00:18:34.260
I'm begging you to please stop
and reconsider it.

00:18:34.327 --> 00:18:36.164
I'll be okay.

00:18:36.231 --> 00:18:38.570
I know I deserve punishment
for what I did.

00:18:38.803 --> 00:18:40.106
Don't do this.

00:18:40.172 --> 00:18:42.745
If something were to happen
to you all because of me...

00:18:42.811 --> 00:18:44.849
It's not for your sake,
Miss Mibu.

00:18:45.116 --> 00:18:46.284
[gasps]

00:18:46.351 --> 00:18:47.353
[Tatsuya] It's because
my neighborhood

00:18:47.420 --> 00:18:49.692
has been targeted by terrorists.

00:18:50.694 --> 00:18:51.461
If anyone dares

00:18:51.529 --> 00:18:53.332
to threaten Miyuki's way
of life,

00:18:53.399 --> 00:18:55.202
I'll eradicate them.

00:18:55.269 --> 00:18:56.706
For me personally,

00:18:56.773 --> 00:18:58.643
that's my top priority.

00:18:58.710 --> 00:19:00.681
[gasps]

00:19:00.747 --> 00:19:01.916
[both gasping]

00:19:01.983 --> 00:19:03.285
‐ Oh.
‐ Hmm.

00:19:06.258 --> 00:19:07.661
[Miyuki] But hold on, Brother.

00:19:08.028 --> 00:19:09.497
How are all of us going

00:19:09.565 --> 00:19:12.036
to locate Blanche's
secret base headquarters?

00:19:12.103 --> 00:19:13.472
If ever you don't
know something,

00:19:13.540 --> 00:19:16.211
all you need to do
is ask somebody who does.

00:19:18.850 --> 00:19:19.819
[gasps]

00:19:19.885 --> 00:19:21.488
‐ [all gasping]
‐ Is that Miss Ono?

00:19:21.556 --> 00:19:22.558
[gasps]

00:19:22.624 --> 00:19:23.793
Well, I...

00:19:24.260 --> 00:19:26.031
[chuckles nervously]

00:19:26.398 --> 00:19:28.603
Why did I ever think
I could remain a detective

00:19:28.670 --> 00:19:30.941
by disciple of Master Kokonoe?

00:19:31.008 --> 00:19:32.511
Pretty naive of me, huh?

00:19:38.055 --> 00:19:39.792
<i>[Tatsuya] An abandoned</i>
<i>factory building?</i>

00:19:39.859 --> 00:19:42.130
It would be better
to go by car.

00:19:42.196 --> 00:19:43.666
We're breaking in head on?

00:19:43.733 --> 00:19:45.069
Correct.

00:19:45.570 --> 00:19:47.306
[Katsuto] I can get that car
for us.

00:19:47.373 --> 00:19:49.645
Huh?
You're going, too, Jumonji?

00:19:49.712 --> 00:19:52.150
As a proud member of one
of the ten master clans,

00:19:52.216 --> 00:19:53.953
it's obviously my duty
to aid them,

00:19:54.020 --> 00:19:55.791
and it goes beyond that.

00:19:55.857 --> 00:19:58.362
As somebody enrolled
at First High School,

00:19:58.429 --> 00:20:00.466
I can't turn a blind eye
to the situation.

00:20:00.534 --> 00:20:02.370
‐ Then I'm‐‐
‐ [Katsuto] Miss Sayagusa.

00:20:02.437 --> 00:20:03.573
You can't go.

00:20:03.640 --> 00:20:04.809
[Mari] The student
council president

00:20:04.875 --> 00:20:06.813
can't be away
at a time like this.

00:20:07.948 --> 00:20:09.417
I guess I agree.

00:20:09.852 --> 00:20:11.021
[Mayumi] But if that's the case,
Mari,

00:20:11.088 --> 00:20:12.490
then you can't go, either.

00:20:12.791 --> 00:20:13.793
After all,

00:20:13.860 --> 00:20:15.362
there might still be
some remnants hiding

00:20:15.429 --> 00:20:16.566
on campus grounds,

00:20:16.632 --> 00:20:18.135
so the disciplinary chairwoman

00:20:18.202 --> 00:20:19.137
should be here as well.

00:20:19.204 --> 00:20:20.540
[groans]

00:20:22.043 --> 00:20:22.945
[Takeaki] Chairman!

00:20:24.815 --> 00:20:26.786
Please bring me along with you
as well.

00:20:27.220 --> 00:20:28.757
Why should I, Kirihara?

00:20:29.324 --> 00:20:32.564
[Takeaki] As a proud student,
I can't let such lawlessness go.

00:20:33.700 --> 00:20:35.403
No good.
I can't bring you.

00:20:35.469 --> 00:20:36.572
[Takeaki] But chairman...

00:20:37.273 --> 00:20:38.475
Not or that reason.

00:20:38.543 --> 00:20:40.212
It's way too flimsy
with lives at stake.

00:20:40.279 --> 00:20:41.783
[groans]

00:20:41.849 --> 00:20:43.152
Now tell the truth.

00:20:43.452 --> 00:20:44.555
Why should I?

00:20:45.156 --> 00:20:46.559
[grunts]

00:20:47.861 --> 00:20:49.030
[Takeaki] Chairman.

00:20:49.532 --> 00:20:52.871
In junior high I always
admired Mibu's sword skills.

00:20:52.938 --> 00:20:55.209
<i>Unlike my own,</i>
<i>which were meant to kill...</i>

00:20:55.877 --> 00:20:58.148
<i>Hers were meant</i>
<i>for pure competition.</i>

00:20:58.215 --> 00:21:00.987
<i>Seeing it was beautiful,</i>
<i>and yet,</i>

00:21:01.054 --> 00:21:02.524
somewhere along the line,

00:21:02.591 --> 00:21:04.427
her swordsmanship
became clouded,

00:21:04.494 --> 00:21:06.799
and it gradually weighed upon
my heart and soul.

00:21:06.866 --> 00:21:09.905
Is that why you pulled a stunt
like luring her into that brawl?

00:21:09.972 --> 00:21:12.076
It's not as if I thought
I was helping Mibu

00:21:12.143 --> 00:21:13.746
to see the error of her ways.

00:21:14.080 --> 00:21:16.819
I just lost my temper
and I picked a fight with her.

00:21:17.253 --> 00:21:20.459
You say the error of her ways,
but wasn't this Mibu's intent?

00:21:20.527 --> 00:21:21.996
No, it wasn't!

00:21:22.063 --> 00:21:25.169
Mibu's true intentions,
her sword's nothing like that.

00:21:25.704 --> 00:21:27.708
Someone messed with her sword.

00:21:28.108 --> 00:21:29.344
Someone corrupted her.

00:21:29.845 --> 00:21:32.049
Some son
of a bitch used Miss Mibu

00:21:32.116 --> 00:21:33.520
in today's incident.

00:21:33.586 --> 00:21:35.857
This isn't even about her,
really.

00:21:35.924 --> 00:21:37.493
I'm just so angry!

00:21:38.095 --> 00:21:39.030
[grunts]

00:21:39.097 --> 00:21:40.567
I'm begging you!

00:21:41.001 --> 00:21:43.640
Jumonji,
please let me come with you!

00:21:44.240 --> 00:21:45.610
[shudders]

00:21:56.331 --> 00:21:57.634
I will allow it.

00:21:57.701 --> 00:22:00.039
[gasps]

00:22:00.406 --> 00:22:01.676
Are you sure?

00:22:02.109 --> 00:22:04.815
Yes, you've now given me
a good enough reason.

00:22:04.882 --> 00:22:06.384
[grunts]

00:22:09.224 --> 00:22:10.627
[Takeaki] Much appreciated.

00:22:12.764 --> 00:22:15.804
<i>[ELISA singing in Japanese]</i>

00:22:15.871 --> 00:22:22.818
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:22:46.197 --> 00:22:52.443
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:22:52.511 --> 00:22:55.182
<i>♪♪ Shape of my love ♪♪</i>

00:22:55.249 --> 00:22:58.155
<i>[singing in Japanese]</i>

00:22:58.222 --> 00:23:05.102
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:23:05.169 --> 00:23:07.708
